        'about-author-page-title': "About the Author <a href=\"presentation.html\" title=\"Back to About\"><img src=\"img/up-arrow.svg\" alt=\"Back to About\" style=\"width:24px; vertical-align:middle; margin-left:8px; opacity:0.8;\"></a>",
        'about-author-lead': "<strong style=\"color:#111;\">Dany Bréelle</strong> holds the French agrégation and a PhD in geography and is the author of the <em>French Names Along the Australian Coastline</em> project.",
        'about-author-bio': "Born in France and educated in Paris, she taught history and geography for 11 years in the French national education system before earning a PhD from Flinders University in 2003. She is now an Associate Researcher in the School of Humanities. Specializing in historical geography, she works on the narratives and nomenclature of major French expeditions in Australia.",
