        'supporters-robinson-bio': "<strong>Professor Guy Robinson</strong>, Vice-President of the RGSSA. A member since 2008, he is a human geographer (Universities of London and Oxford) with 45+ years of research on rural development and environmental management. Formerly at the University of Edinburgh (recipient of the Royal Scottish Geographical Society President’s Medal), past President of the British Australian Studies Association, and visiting scholar at several Australasian universities (Canterbury, Melbourne, Newcastle, New South Wales, Otago). At UniSA he led the Centre for Regional Engagement (2010–2014). He is now Departmental Associate at the University of Cambridge (Land Economy), Adjunct Professor at the University of Adelaide (Geography, Environment and Population), and Editor of <em>Research in Globalization</em>.",
